		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><addressee>Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Cura&#231;ao</placeName> <date>9 <sic>Yany</sic> 1856</date></p>
				<p>Rev Sir&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">I am in receipt of your<lb/> valued lines of the <date>2d</date> Ulto. And am happy to per<lb/>ceive from the same your good health &#38; I<lb/> <sic>inclose</sic> you hereby a Bill to your favor for &#36;107.84<lb/> against <persName>Messrs Bomen Graves &#38; Co</persName> <placeName>N&#47;Y</placeName>&#44; from said<lb/> amt. You will take off for your a&#47;c &#36;74.50 of<lb/> the books which I have sold&#59; and the balance<lb/> of &#36;33. 34 your will oblige me to hand to <persName>Messr<lb/> J. M Moss &#38; Brother</persName>&#44; with the letters <sic>inclosed</sic>.<lb/> I have to conclude for to day for not <sic>haveing</sic><lb/> time&#44;</p> 
			<p rend="indent(2)">remaining yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">B deCasseres Jr</persName></p>
				<p>NB.</p>
				<p>I have wrote you several times<lb/> about the Occident of <date>May</date> which was not received&#44;<lb/> please send them&#44; that I may give to the subscribers<lb/> also please to join with the occident one of <sic>jewish</sic> Ad<lb/>vocate.  <persName>Rev&#58; Choemacieu<add>&#63;</add></persName> send his compliment<lb/> to you.</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName><hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi></placeName></p>
		</body>
